descript.abstract: The Component Trees To Manage table lists the trees commonly recommended for managing on the referenced map unit component.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.1.1.3143

attr.attrdef: A non-connotative string of characters used to uniquely identify a record in the Component Trees To Manage table.
A generally accepted common name used for a plant in a geographic region, usually a state.
The unique identifier of a record in the Component table. Use this column to join the Component Trees To Manage table to the Component table.
The full genus and species name as listed in the PLANTS Database, USDA-NRCS, National Plant Data Center.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: A unique symbol used to identify a plant genus or a plant species. (The PLANTS Database, USDA-NRCS, National Plant Data Center.)

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standard for Digital Geospatial Metadata
